     Curated list of Mastodon-related stuff!

   Mastodon is the world's largest free, open-source, decentralized
   microblogging network. See the
   [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-mastodon#
   official]Official and
   [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-mastodon#
   documentation]Documentation categories to learn more about the network.

Contents

     * Official
     * Documentation
     * Clients
     * Tools
     * User styles
     * User scripts
     * Bots
     * News & magazines bots
     * Associations
     * Blogs
     * Librairies

Official

     * [https://joinmastodon.org/]Website
     * [https://github.com/tootsuite/mastodon]GitHub repository
     * [https://github.com/tootsuite/documentation/blob/master/Using-Masto
       don/FAQ.md]Frequently Asked Questions

Documentation

     * [https://hackernoon.com/what-i-wish-i-knew-before-joining-mastodon-
       7a17e7f12a2b]What I wish I knew before joining Mastodon -
       Introduction to Mastodon.
     * [http://cassolotl.tumblr.com/post/161825902540]Mastodon tutorial -
       Quick Mastodon tutorial.
     * [https://en.mstdn.wiki/Main_Page]Wiki - The Mastodon Community
       Wiki.
     * [https://github.com/tootsuite/documentation/blob/master/Using-the-A
       PI/API.md]API overview

Clients

     * [https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.keylesspalace.tu
       sky]Tusky - Android client.
     * [https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=ch.kevinegli.tootyfr
       uity221258]TootyFruity - Android app for Mastodon.
     * [https://f-droid.org/packages/org.mariotaku.twidere/]Twidere -
       Android app for Twitter, GNU Social and Mastodon.
     * [https://github.com/n1k0/tooty]Tooty - Experimental multi-account
       Mastodon Web client (Elm).
     * [https://itunes.apple.com/app/id1229531204]Mustor - iOS app for
       Mastodon.
     * [https://github.com/ihabunek/toot]toot - Mastodon CLI client
       (Python).
     * [https://github.com/McKael/madonctl]madonctl - Mastodon CLI client
       (Go).
     * [https://github.com/naumanni/naumanni]naumanni - Web user interface
       specially designed for Mastodon.
     * [https://github.com/dysk0/harbour-tooter]Tooter - Native client for
       SailfishOS.
     * [http://tootdon.club/]Tootdon - Fully featured client for iOS and
       Android.

Tools

     * [https://instances.social/list]Mastodon instances - List of
       Mastodon instances.
     * [https://bridge.joinmastodon.org/]Mastodon bridge - Find your
       Twitter friends in the federated Mastodon network.
     * [http://www.unmung.com/mastoview]unmung.com/mastoview - Preview the
       local or federated timeline of any instance.
     * [https://scheduler.mastodon.tools/]Toot scheduler - Schedule now,
       toot later.
     * [https://dashboards.mnm.social/]Mastodon Network Monitoring (MNM) -
       Track and display browsable stats about the Mastodon network.
     * [https://framagit.org/luc/last]Last - Aggregate toots on a web page
       providing Atom feed and an epub (Perl).

User styles

     * [https://userstyles.org/styles/139721/mastodon-variable-width]Varia
       ble width - Makes Mastodon scale with the browser's width.
     * [https://userstyles.org/styles/141457/mastodon-dynamic-wide-columns
       -narrow-drawer]Narrow drawer - With the variable width style, makes
       the drawer narrower and the other columns scale accordingly.

User scripts

     * [https://greasyfork.org/fr/scripts/29228-mastodon-nsfw-remover]NSFW
       Remover - Automatically display NSFW images.
     * [https://openuserjs.org/scripts/bl00m/Mastodon_Customizable_Interfa
       ce]Customizable interface - Move and resize columns on a grid.
     * [https://gitlab.com/pmorinerie/birdsite]BirdSite - Browser
       extension for cross-posting Mastodon toots to Twitter.

Bots

     * [https://gitlab.com/chaica/feed2toot]feed2toot - Automatically
       parses RSS feeds, identifies new posts and posts them on Mastodon
       (Python).
     * [https://github.com/josefkenny/usercount]usercount - Bot which
       posts user statistics to Mastodon (Python).
     * [https://github.com/gled-rs/mastodon-autofollow]autofollow -
       Autofollow bot for Mastodon (Python).
     * [https://github.com/raymestalez/mastodon-hnbot]hnbot - Posts the
       Hacker News stories with 100+ points (Python).
     * [https://christopher.su/projects/translator/]translator - Translate
       any toot into the desired language using @translator@toot.works
       [langcode].
     * [https://mastodon.social/@TrendingBot]@TrendingBot@mastodon.social
       - Shows you what's trending on Mastodon.
     * [https://gitlab.com/chaica/remindr]Remindr - Automatically send
       reminders to both Mastodon and Twitter from a list of resources
       (Python).
     * [https://botsin.space/@newsbot]News Bot - mirrors Twitter accounts
       on Mastodon (ClojureScript), source available on
       [https://github.com/yogthos/mastodon-bot]GitHub.

News & magazines bots

   Please note: most of them are non-official. Also, we do not recommend
   any, they are just listed here for your information.

English

     * [https://status.fsf.org/fsf]@fsf@status.fsf.org - FSF Free Software
       Foundation.
     * [https://mastodon.social/@HackerNewsBot]@HackerNewsBot@mastodon.soc
       ial - Hacker News.
     * [https://apoil.org/@nasa]@nasa@apoil.org - NASA.
     * [https://quitter.im/newsstream]@newsstream@quitter.im - NewsStream.
     * [https://mastodon.blue/@openrightsgroupbot]@openrightsgroupbot@mast
       odon.blue - Open Rights Group.
     * [https://framapiaf.org/@btc]@btc@framapiaf.org - News about the
       Bitcoin Cryptocurrency (marketcap, community, rise/drop alerts).
     * [https://framapiaf.org/@ethereum]@ethereum@framapiaf.org - News
       about the Ethereum Cryptocurrency (marketcap, community, rise/drop
       alerts).
     * [https://framapiaf.org/@monero]@monero@framapiaf.org - News about
       the Monero Cryptocurrency (marketcap, community, rise/drop alerts).
     * [https://3.nu/@tedtalks]@tedtalks@3.nu - TED Talks.

